  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ocean carbon sources and sinks</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The ocean absorbs up to 30% of the annual emissions of CO2 to the atmosphere, alleviating the impacts of climate change (CC). This comes at a steep ecological cost, as the absorbed CO2 results in changing acidity levels in the ocean. IOC is custodian agency for the SDG target indicator 14.3.1. To equip MS with the tools to adapt to and mitigate the impacts of ocean acidification, IOC supports the GOA-ON. Further, IOC co-sponsors the Blue Carbon Initiative, which aims to raise awareness for the importance of mangroves, tidal marshes and seagrasses, as a possible nature-based solution for CC and the potential contribution to NDCs under the Paris Agreement, if their protection and restoration are based on the latest science.</narrative>
  </description>
